THE Sweetie My Baby hitmaker has been found guilty of rape committed in the  year 2013. Sipho Charles Ndlovu, known by his fans as Brickz, heard the news on Friday, as he stood in the Roodepoort Magistrates  Court.During one of Brickz’s court appearances, his legal representative had said the case against his client was “weak and full of holes”.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>But Magistrate John Baloyi said the kwaito star had failed to convince the court that he did not commit the crime.Brickz’s R50 000 bail was revoked, and the star was then locked up in a holding cell. He will remain in custody until he is sentenced.This is expected to happen on 20 July, as the lengthy legal process is brought to an end.The 32-year-old musician was arrested in 2013 after raping a teenage relative at his home in Honeydew, Joburg.It was reported that the girl was a regular visitor to Brickz’s house.At the time, it was reported that the kwaito star’s wife, Nqobile Ndlovu, reported him to the police after questioning the girl.The state’s case included the allegation that Brickz entered a bedroom where the girl was eating her lunch.According to the state, he pushed her onto the bed, raped her, then threatened to kill her if she told anyone.Reports say Nqobile noticed that the girl had begun to act strangely. And the teenager eventually said the kwaito star had raped her.Both Nqobile and the girl’s dad reportedly went to the police station to lay a charge of rape.The singer had started getting back into making music in 2015. In the same year, he was arrested and charged with assault after allegedly threatening to kill his lover.